
[1]seizure

   SE'IZURE, n.

   1. The act of seizing; the act of laying hold on suddenly; as the
   seizure of a thief.

   2. The act of taking possession by force; as the seizure of lands or
   goods; the seizureof a town by an enemy; the seizure of a throne by a
   usurper.

   3. The act of taking by warrant; as the seizure of contraband goods.

   4. The thing taken or seized.

   5. Gripe; grasp; possession.

   And give me seizure of the mighty wealth. Dryden.

   6. Catch; a catching.

   let there be no sudden seizure of a lapsed syllable, to play upon it.
   Watts.
